    "recap_headline": "University of Kansas Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FORT WORTH, Texas \u2013\nKansas and No. 17 TCU were in the top of the ninth inning Tuesday before inclement weather moved into the area to halt play. The game will be resumed on Wednesday at 12 p.m. CT.\nWhen the game resumes, Kansas will trail 9-2 with one out in the top of the ninth.\nDylan Schlotterback\nwill be at the plate, with\nDariel Osoria\nat third base and\nAugusto Mungarrieta\nat second base.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\n\u2022 TCU scored an unearned run in the first inning on a sacrifice fly to take a 1-0 lead.\n\u2022 The Horned Frogs extended their advantage to 3-0 in the second inning. The first run came in to score on a throwing error and another run scored on a balk.\n\u2022 TCU stretched its lead with a five-run fourth inning. A run scored on an RBI single by Cole Cramer and Chase Brunson hit a grand slam to make it an 8-0 game.\n\u2022 Another run scored in the sixth inning on an RBI triple off the bat of Sawyer Strosnider. That brought the score to 9-0.\n\u2022 Kansas scored two runs in the top of the ninth inning before weather rolled in. Osoria had an RBI single and Mungarrieta hit an RBI double to make it 9-2."
